Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: WeeksGestationatBirth
Description: Numeric value used to describe the number of weeks starting from the approximate date of the biological mother's last menstrual period and ending with the birth of the patient.

Label: VitalStatus
Description: The survival state of the person registered on the protocol.

Label: AgeIsObfuscated
Description: The age of the patient has been modified for compliance reasons. The actual age differs from what is reported. Other date intervals for this patient may also be modified.

Label: OccupationDurationYears
Description: The number of years a patient worked in a specific occupation.

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: PrematureAtBirth
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient was premature (less than 37 weeks gestation) at birth.

Label: Ethnicity
Description: An individual's self-described social and cultural grouping, specifically whether an individual describes themselves as Hispanic or Latino. The provided values are based on the categories defined by the U.S. Office of Management and Business and used by the U.S. Census Bureau.
Valid Values: ['not hispanic or latino', 'unknown', 'not allowed to collect', 'Not Reported', 'hispanic or latino']

Label: Gender
Description: Text designations that identify gender. Gender is described as the assemblage of properties that distinguish people on the basis of their societal roles. [Identification of gender is based upon self-report and may come from a form, questionnaire, interview, etc.]

Label: Race
Description: An arbitrary classification of a taxonomic group that is a division of a species. It usually arises as a consequence of geographical isolation withina a species and is characterized by shared heredity, physical attributes and behavior, and in the case of humans, by common history, nationality, or geographic distribution.
Valid Values: ['unknown', 'american indian or alaska native', 'native hawaiian or other pacific islander', 'not allowed to collect', 'Not Reported', 'Other', 'black or african american', 'asian', 'white']

Label: AlcoholExposure
Description: Indicate if individual has alcohol exposure

Label: AsbestosExposure
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient was exposed to asbestos.

Label: StartDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the date of birth (index date) to the date of an event (e.g. exposure to environmental factor, treatment start, etc.). If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: SmokingExposure
Description: Indicate if individual has smoking exposure

Label: RespirableCrystallineSilicaExposure
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether a patient was exposured to respirable crystalline silica, a widespread, naturally occurring, crystalline metal oxide that consists of different forms including quartz, cristobalite, tridymite, tripoli, ganister, chert and novaculite.

Label: EnvironmentalTobaccoSmokeExposure
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether a patient was exposed to smoke that is emitted from burning tobacco, including cigarettes, pipes, and cigars. This includes tobacco smoke exhaled by smokers.

Label: RadonExposure
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient was exposed to radon.

Label: CoalDustExposure
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether a patient was exposed to fine powder derived by the crushing of coal.

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: AlcoholHistory
Description: A response to a question that asks whether the participant has consumed at least 12 drinks of any kind of alcoholic beverage in their lifetime.

Label: AlcoholIntensity
Description: Category to describe the patient's current level of alcohol use as self-reported by the patient.

Label: AlcoholType
Description: Type of alcohol use

Label: AlcoholDaysPerWeek
Description: Numeric value used to describe the average number of days each week that a person consumes an alcoholic beverage.

Label: AlcoholDrinksPerDay
Description: Numeric value used to describe the average number of alcoholic beverages a person consumes per day.

Label: TobaccoUseperDay
Description: Numeric value that represents the number of times the patient uses tobacco each day.

Label: TobaccoSmokingQuitYear
Description: The year in which the participant quit smoking.

Label: SmokingFrequency
Description: The text term used to generally decribe how often the patient smokes.

Label: SecondhandSmokeasChild
Description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient was exposed to secondhand smoke as a child.

Label: YearsSmoked
Description: Numeric value (or unknown) to represent the number of years a person has been smoking.

Attribute: Time between Waking and First Smoke

Label: FEV1RefPreBronchPercent
Description: The percentage comparison to a normal value reference range of the volume of air that a patient can forcibly exhale from the lungs in one second pre-bronchodilator.

Label: HPVPositiveType
Description: Text classification to represent the strain or type of human papillomavirus identified in an individual.

Label: HIVViralLoad
Description: Numeric value that represents the concentration of an analyte or aliquot extracted from the sample or sample portion, measured in milligrams per milliliter.

Label: ViralHepatitisSerologies
Description: Text term that describes the kind of serological laboratory test used to determine the patient's hepatitus status.
Valid Values: ['Hepatitis C Virus RNA', 'unknown', 'Hepatitis B Surface Antigen', 'HBV DNA', 'Not Reported', 'HBV Core Antibody', 'HBV Surface Antibody', 'HBV Genotype', 'HCV Genotype', 'Hepatitis C Antibody', '']

Label: ImagingResult
Description: The text term used to describe the result of the imaging or scan performed on the patient.

Label: ECOGPerformanceStatus
Description: The ECOG functional performance status of the patient/participant.

Label: RefluxTreatmentType
Description: Text term used to describe the types of treatment used to manage gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD).
Valid Values: ['Not Applicable', 'Medically Treated', 'unknown', 'No Treatment', 'H2 Blockers', 'Not Reported', 'Proton Pump Inhibitors', 'Surgically Treated', 'Antacids', '']

Label: HysterectomyType
Description: The text term used to describe the type of hysterectomy the patient had.

Label: ScanTracerUsed
Description: The text term used to describe the type of tracer used during the imaging or scan of the patient.

Label: RiskFactorTreatment
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient received treatment for a risk factor the patient had at the time of or prior to their diagnosis.

Label: KarnofskyPerformanceStatus
Description: Text term used to describe the classification used of the functional capabilities of a person.

Label: PancreatitisOnsetYear
Description: Date of onset of pancreatitis.

Label: ImagingType
Description: The text term used to describe the type of imaging or scan performed on the patient.

Label: NadirCD4Count
Description: Numeric value that represents the lowest point to which the CD4 count has dropped (nadir).

Label: DiseaseResponse
Description: Code assigned to describe the patient's response or outcome to the disease.

Label: IGCCCGStage
Description: The text term used to describe the International Germ Cell Cancer Collaborative Group (IGCCCG), a grouping used to further classify metastatic testicular tumors.

Label: Laterality
Description: For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the cancer originates.

Label: TumorDepth
Description: Numeric value that represents the depth of tumor invasion, measured in millimeters (mm).

Label: PercentTumorInvasion
Description: The percentage of tumor cells spread locally in a malignant neoplasm through infiltration or destruction of adjacent tissue.

Label: GleasonGradeGroup
Description: The text term used to describe the overall grouping of grades defined by the Gleason grading classification, which is used to determine the aggressiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

Label: PerineuralInvasionPresent
Description: A yes/no indicator to ask if perineural invasion or infiltration of tumor or cancer is present.

Label: VascularInvasionType
Description: Text term that represents the type of vascular tumor invasion.

Label: GleasonPatternsPercent
Description: Numeric value that represents the percentage of Patterns 4 and 5, which is used when the Gleason score is greater than 7 to predict prognosis.

Label: NonNodalTumorDeposits
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe the presence of tumor deposits in the pericolic or perirectal fat or in adjacent mesentery away from the leading edge of the tumor.

Label: AgeatDiagnosis
Description: Age at the time of diagnosis expressed in number of days since birth.

Label: MarginDistance
Description: Numeric value (in centimeters) that represents the distance between the tumor and the surgical margin.

Label: MitosisKaryorrhexisIndex
Description: Text term that represents the component of the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC) for mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI).

Label: IRSStage
Description: The text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma tumors, as defined by the Intergroup Rhabdomyosarcoma Study (IRS).

Label: AJCCPathologicStage
Description: The extent of a cancer, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to other parts of the body based on AJCC staging criteria.
Valid Values: ['Stage IA1', 'Stage IIIC', 'Stage II', 'Stage IB2', 'Stage IIIC2', 'Stage IB1', 'Stage 0a', 'Stage IIA', 'Stage Tis', 'Stage IVB', 'Stage X', 'Stage IIA1', 'Stage IVA', 'Stage IVC', 'Stage 0', 'Stage IS', 'Stage 0is', 'Stage IIC', 'Stage IV', 'Stage IIB', 'Stage IIIC1', 'Stage IIIA', 'Stage III', 'Stage IC', 'Stage IIA2', 'Stage IA2', 'unknown', 'Stage IIIB', 'Stage IA', 'Not Reported', 'Stage IB', 'Stage I', 'Stage IIC1', '']

Unnamed: 0: Tumor Confined to Organ of Origin
Attribute: Tumor Confined to Organ of Origin
Label: TumorConfinedtoOrganofOrigin
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the tumor is confined to the organ where it originated and did not spread to a proximal or distant location within the body.

Label: ResidualDisease
Description: Text terms to describe the status of a tissue margin following surgical resection.

Label: MetastasisatDiagnosis
Description: The text term used to describe the extent of metastatic disease present at diagnosis.

Label: PrimaryGleasonGrade
Description: The text term used to describe the primary Gleason score, which describes the pattern of cells making up the largest area of the tumor. The primary and secondary Gleason pattern grades are combined to determine the patient's Gleason grade group, which is used to determine the aggresiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

Label: BreslowThickness
Description: The number that describes the distance, in millimeters, between the upper layer of the epidermis and the deepest point of tumor penetration.

Label: LymphaticInvasionPresent
Description: A yes/no indicator to ask if small or thin-walled vessel invasion is present, indicating lymphatic involvement

Label: AJCCStagingSystemEdition
Description: The text term used to describe the version or edition of the American Joint Committee on Cancer Staging Handbooks, a publication by the group formed for the purpose of developing a system of staging for cancer that is acceptable to the American medical profession and is compatible with other accepted classifications.

Unnamed: 0: Days to Last Known Disease Status
Attribute: Days to Last Known Disease Status
Label: DaystoLastKnownDiseaseStatus
Description: Time interval from the date of last follow up to the date of initial pathologic diagnosis, represented as a calculated number of days. If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: LastKnownDiseaseStatus
Description: Text term that describes the last known state or condition of an individual's neoplasm.
Valid Values: ['Loco-regional recurrence/progression', 'Not Applicable', 'Not Allowed To Collect', 'Not Reported', 'unknown tumor status', 'Distant met recurrence/progression', 'Tumor free', 'With tumor', 'Biochemical evidence of disease without structural correlate']

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: AnaplasiaPresentType
Description: The text term used to describe the morphologic findings indicating the presence of a malignant cellular infiltrate characterized by the presence of large pleomorphic cells, necrosis, and high mitotic activity in a tissue sample.

Label: AJCCPathologicN
Description: The codes that represent the stage of cancer based on the nodes present (N stage) according to criteria based on multiple editions of the AJCC's Cancer Staging Manual.

Label: CogRhabdomyosarcomaRiskGroup
Description: Text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma, as defined by the Children's Oncology Group (COG).

Label: WHOCNSGrade
Description: WHO CNS Grade
Valid Values: ['unknown', 'Grade I', 'Grade III', 'Not Reported', 'Grade Not Assigned', 'Grade II', 'Grade IV', '']

Label: GreatestTumorDimension
Description: Numeric value that represents the measurement of the widest portion of the tumor in centimeters.

Label: AnaplasiaPresent
Description: Yes/no/unknown/Not Reported indicator used to describe whether anaplasia was present at the time of diagnosis.

Label: DaystoLastFollowup
Description: Time interval from the date of last follow up to the date of initial pathologic diagnosis, represented as a calculated number of days. If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: DaystoDiagnosis
Description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient was diagnosed with the malignant disease. If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: AJCCPathologicT
Description: Code of pathological T (primary tumor) to define the size or contiguous extension of the primary tumor (T), using staging criteria from the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC).

Label: InternationalPrognosticIndex
Description: The text term used to describe the International Prognostic Index, which classifies the prognosis of patients with aggressive non-Hodgkin's lymphoma.

Label: ClassificationofTumor
Description: Text that describes the kind of disease present in the tumor specimen as related to a specific timepoint.

Label: LymphNodeInvolvedSite
Description: The text term used to describe the anatomic site of lymph node involvement.

Label: FirstSymptomPriortoDiagnosis
Description: Text term used to describe the patient's first symptom experienced prior to diagnosis and thought to be related to the disease.
Valid Values: ['unknown', 'Motor or Movement Changes', 'Visual Changes', 'Sensory Changes', 'Not Reported', 'Seizures', 'Altered Mental Status', 'Headaches', '']

Label: TumorFocality
Description: The text term used to describe whether the patient's disease originated in a single location or multiple locations.

Label: MitoticCount
Description: The number of mitoses identified under the microscope in tumors. The method of counting varies, according to the specific tumor examined. Usually, the mitotic count is determined based on the number of mitoses per high power field (40X) or 10 high power fields.

Label: MedulloblastomaMolecularClassification
Description: The text term used to describe the classification of medulloblastoma tumors based on molecular features.

Label: SynchronousMalignancy
Description: A yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient had an additional malignant diagnosis at the same time the tumor used for sequencing was diagnosed. If both tumors were sequenced, both tumors would have synchronous malignancies.

Label: PrecancerousConditionType
Description: The classification of pre-cancerous cells found in a specific collection of data being studied by the Consortium for Molecular and Cellular Characterization of Screen-Detected Lesions (MCL).

The primary and secondary Gleason pattern grades are combined to determine the patient's Gleason grade group, which is used to determine the aggresiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

Label: MethodofDiagnosis

Label: INRGStage

Label: LymphNodesTested

Label: PriorTreatment
Description: A yes/no/unknown/not applicable indicator related to the administration of therapeutic agents received before the body specimen was collected.

Label: TumorGrade

Label: OvarianSpecimenStatus

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: AJCCClinicalN
Description: Extent of the regional lymph node involvement for the cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.

Label: WHONTEGrade
Description: WHO NTE Grade

Label: AJCCClinicalT
Description: Extent of the primary cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.

Label: SupratentorialLocalization
Description: Text term to specify the location of the supratentorial tumor.

Label: PregnantatDiagnosis
Description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient was pregnant at the time they were diagnosed.

Label: GleasonGradeTertiary
Description: The text term used to describe the tertiary pattern as described by the Gleason Grading System.

Label: INPCHistologicGroup
Description: The text term used to describe the classification of neuroblastomas distinguishing between favorable and unfavorable histologic groups. The histologic score, defined by the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC), is based on age, mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI), stromal content and degree of tumor cell differentiation.

Label: PeritonealFluidCytologicalStatus
Description: The text term used to describe the malignant status of the peritoneal fluid determined by cytologic testing.

Label: TumorLargestDimensionDiameter
Description: Numeric value used to describe the maximum diameter or dimension of the primary tumor, measured in centimeters.

Label: Morphology
Description: The third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000 used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms. The study of the structure of the cells and their arrangement to constitute tissues and, finally, the association among these to form organs. In pathology, the microscopic process of identifying normal and abnormal morphologic characteristics in tissues, by employing various cytochemical and immunocytochemical stains. A system of numbered categories for representation of data.

Label: OvarianSurfaceInvolvement
Description: The text term that describes whether the surface tissue (outer boundary) of the ovary shows evidence of involvement or presence of cancer.

Label: MicropapillaryFeatures
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether micropapillary features were determined to be present.

Label: VascularInvasionPresent
Description: The yes/no indicator to ask if large vessel or venous invasion was detected by surgery or presence in a tumor specimen.
Valid Values: ['unknown', 'Not Allowed To Collect', 'Not Reported', 'Yes - Vascular Invasion Present', 'no', '']

Label: BestOverallResponse

Label: INPCGrade

Description: The text term used to describe the reason a specific treatment or regimen ended.
Valid Values: ['Withdrawal by Subject', 'Course of Therapy Completed', 'Disease Progression', 'Adverse Therapy Event', 'Death', 'Other', '']

Label: TreatmentEffectIndicator
Description: The text term used to indicate whether the treatment had an effect on the patient.

Label: TreatmentOutcome
Description: Text term that describes the patient's final outcome after the treatment was administered.
Valid Values: ['Partial Response', 'No Response', 'unknown', 'Stable Disease', 'Treatment Ongoing', 'Very Good Partial Response', 'Persistent Disease', 'Mixed Response', 'Complete Response', 'Not Reported', 'Treatment Stopped Due to Toxicity', 'Progressive Disease', 'No Measurable Disease', '']

Label: TreatmentArm
Description: Text term used to describe the treatment arm assigned to a patient at the time eligibility is determined.

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: TherapeuticAgents
Description: Text identification of the individual agent(s) used as part of a treatment regimen.

Label: TreatmentorTherapy
Description: A yes/no/unknown/not applicable indicator related to the administration of therapeutic agents received.

Label: ChemoConcurrenttoRadiation
Description: The text term used to describe whether the patient was receiving chemotherapy concurrent to radiation.

Label: TreatmentFrequency
Description: The text term used to describe the frequency the patient received an agent or regimen.
Valid Values: ['Every Hour', 'unknown', 'Twice Daily', 'Every Other Day', 'Once Weekly', 'Not Reported', 'Four Times Daily', 'Three Times Daily', 'Five Times Daily', 'Twice Weekly', 'Every 24 Hours', '']

Label: NumberofCycles
Description: The numeric value used to describe the number of cycles of a specific treatment or regimen the patient received.

Label: HistoneVariant
Description: The text term used to describe a specific histone variants, which are proteins that substitute for the core canonical histones.

Label: MolecularAnalysisMethod
Description: The text term used to describe the method used for molecular analysis. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.
Valid Values: ['ISH', 'Sequencing NOS', 'Comparative Genomic Hybridization', 'WGS', 'Microarray', 'Cytogenetics NOS', 'FISH', 'Southern Blotting', 'Flow Cytometry', 'Targeted Sequencing', 'Microsatellite Analysis', 'IHC', 'RT-PCR', 'Karyotype', 'WXS', 'RNA Sequencing', 'Other', 'Nuclear Staining', 'Not Applicable', 'unknown', 'Not Reported']

Label: Locus
Description: Alphanumeric value used to describe the locus of a specific genetic variant. Example: NM_001126114.

Label: CellCount
Description: Numeric value used to describe the number of cells used for molecular testing. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: Cytoband
Description: Alphanumeric value used to describe the cytoband or chromosomal location targeted or included in molecular analysis. If a specific genetic variant is being reported, this property can be used to capture the cytoband where the variant is located. Format: [chromosome][chromosome arm].[band+sub-bands]. Example: 17p13.1. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: Exon
Description: Exon number targeted or included in a molecular analysis. If a specific genetic variant is being reported, this property can be used to capture the exon where that variant is located. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: MismatchRepairMutation
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the mutation included in molecular testing was known to have an affect on the mismatch repair process. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: Pathogenicity

Label: TestValue
Description: The text term or numeric value used to describe a specific result of a molecular test. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here

Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: ClinicalBiospecimenType

Label: AAChange

Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Label: TimepointLabel

Label: Ploidy

Label: SecondGeneSymbol
Description: The text term used to describe a secondary gene targeted or included in molecular analysis. For rearrangements, this is should represent the location of the variant. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: HistoneFamily
Description: The text term used to describe the family, or classification of a group of basic proteins found in chromatin, called histones.

Label: TestResult
Description: The text term used to describe the result of the molecular test. If the test result was a numeric value see test_value. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.
Valid Values: ['Not Applicable', 'positive', 'unknown', 'Test Value Reported', 'Normal', 'negative', 'Loss of Expression', 'High', 'Low', 'Copy Number Reported', 'Not Reported', 'Equivocal', 'Abnormal NOS', 'Intermediate', 'Overexpressed']

Label: LociCount
Description: Numeric value used to describe the number of loci tested.

Label: VariantType
Description: The text term used to describe the type of genetic variation.

Label: StartDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the date of birth (index date) to the date of an event (e.g. exposure to environmental factor, treatment start, etc.). If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: SecondExon
Description: The second exon number involved in molecular variation. If a specific genetic variant is being reported, this property can be used to capture the second exon where that variant is located. This property is typically used for a translocation where two different locations are involved in the variation.

Label: Zygosity
Description: The text term used to describe the zygosity of a specific genetic variant.

Label: VariantOrigin
Description: The text term used to describe the biological origin of a specific genetic variant. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: Chromosome
Description: The text term used to describe a chromosome targeted or included in molecular testing. If a specific genetic variant is being reported, this property can be used to capture the chromosome where that variant is located. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: LociAbnormalCount
Description: Numeric value used to describe the number of loci determined to be abnormal.

Label: BloodTestNormalRangeUpper
Description: Numeric value used to describe the upper limit of the normal range used to describe a healthy individual at the institution where the test was completed.

Label: CopyNumber
Description: Numeric value used to describe the number of times a section of the genome is repeated or copied within an insertion, duplication or deletion variant. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: MolecularConsequence
Description: The text term used to describe the molecular consequence of genetic variation. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.
Valid Values: ['Upstream Gene Variant', 'TF Binding Site Variant', 'Intron Variant', 'Stop Gain', 'Intergenic Variant', 'Splice Acceptor Variant', 'Stop Lost', 'Regulatory Region Ablation', 'TFBS Ablation', '5 Prime UTR Variant', 'Splice Donor Variant', 'Transcript Amplification', 'Mature miRNA Variant', 'Feature Elongation', 'Coding Sequence Variant', 'Inframe Insertion', 'Protein Altering Variant', 'Non-coding Transcript Variant', 'Feature Truncation', 'Missense Variant', 'Start Lost', 'TFBS Amplification', 'Transcript Ablation', 'Incomplete Terminal Codon Variant', 'Downstream Gene Variant', 'NMD Transcript Variant', 'Non-coding Transcript Exon Variant', 'Regulatory Region Amplification', 'Splice Region Variant', '3 Prime UTR Variant', 'Frameshift Variant', 'Regulatory Region Variant', 'Stop Retained Variant', 'Synonymous Variant', 'Inframe Deletion', '']

Label: TestUnits
Description: The text term used to describe the units of the test value for a molecular test. This property is used in conjunction with test_value. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: SpecializedMolecularTest
Description: Text term used to describe a specific test that is not covered in the list of molecular analysis methods. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: Clonality
Description: The text term used to describe whether a genomic variant is related by descent from a single progenitor cell. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: Transcript
Description: Alphanumeric value used to describe the transcript of a specific genetic variant. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: GeneSymbol
Description: The text term used to describe a gene targeted or included in molecular analysis. For rearrangements, this is should be used to represent the reference gene. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: Antigen
Description: The text term used to describe an antigen included in molecular testing. Note: This node is meant to capture molecular tests that were completed clinically for the participant and only includes data from diagnostic array that was completed prior to research sequencing was done. Do not include data related to research assay outputs here.

Label: CollectionDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the research participant's index date that the biospecimen was obtained. If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: FixativeType
Description: Text term to identify the type of fixative used to preserve a tissue specimen
Valid Values: ["Carnoy's Fixative", 'Methacarn', 'Carbodiimide', 'Formalin', 'OCT media', 'Para-benzoquinone', 'Alcohol', 'Unfixed', 'None', 'Cryo-store', 'Dimidoester', '95% Ethanol', 'Other', 'NP40 lysis buffer', 'Saline', 'RNAlater', 'unknown', 'TCL lysis buffer', 'Dimethylacetamide', 'Acetone', 'Glutaraldehyde', 'Polaxamer', 'PAXgene tissue']

Label: NumberProliferatingCells
Description: Numeric value that represents the count of proliferating cells determined during pathologic review of the sample slide(s).

Label: PercentMonocyteInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of monocyte infiltration in a sample or specimen.

Label: HTANParentID
Description: HTAN ID of parent from which the biospecimen was obtained. Parent could be another biospecimen or a research participant.

Label: AcquisitionMethodType
Description: Records the method of acquisition or source for the specimen under consideration.
Valid Values: ['Biopsy', 'Other Acquisition Method', 'Punch Biopsy', 'Autopsy', 'Blood draw', 'Endoscopic biopsy', 'Induced sputum', 'Lymphadenectomy - Regional Nodes', 'Non induced sputum', 'Forceps biopsy', 'Surgical Resection', 'Not specified', 'Sentinel Node Biopsy', 'Excision', 'Cytobrush', 'Re-excision', 'Shave Biopsy', 'Fine Needle Aspirate', 'BAL (bronchial alveolar lavage)', 'Core needle biopsy', 'Fluid collection']

Label: PercentTumorNuclei
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of tumor nuclei in a malignant neoplasm sample or specimen.

Label: ProtocolLink
Description: Protocols.io ID or DOI link to a free/open protocol resource describing in detail the assay protocol (e.g. surface markers used in Smart-seq, dissociation duration,  lot/batch numbers for key reagents such as primers, sequencing reagent kits, etc.) or the protocol by which the sample was obtained or generated.

Label: SourceHTANBiospecimenID
Description: This is the HTAN ID that may have been assigned to the biospecimen at the site of biospecimen origin (e.g. BU).

Label: PercentStromalCells
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of reactive cells that are present in a malignant tumor sample or specimen but are not malignant such as fibroblasts, vascular structures, etc.

Label: SlicingMethod
Description: Imaging specific: the method by which the tissue was sliced.

Label: PercentNecrosis
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of cell death in a malignant tumor sample or specimen.

Label: StorageMethod
Description: The method by which a biomaterial was stored after preservation or before another protocol was used.
Valid Values: ['Refrigerated vacuum chamber', 'Fresh', 'Paraffin block', 'Frozen in vapor phase', 'Frozen in liquid nitrogen', 'Refrigerated at 4 degrees', 'Desiccant at 4C', 'Frozen at -80C', 'Frozen at -70C', 'Cut slide', 'Frozen at -20C', 'Ambient temperature', 'RNAlater at 25C', 'RNAlater at 4C', 'RNAlater at -20C', '4C in vacuum chamber', 'Not Applicable', 'unknown', 'Frozen at -150C']

Label: ProcessingDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the research participant's index date that the biospecimen was processed. If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: DysplasiaFraction
Description: Resulting value to represent the number of pieces of dysplasia divided by the total number of pieces. [Text: max length 5]

Label: DegreeofDysplasia
Description: Information related to the presence of cells that look abnormal under a microscope but are not cancer. Records the degree of dysplasia for the cyst or lesion under consideration.
Valid Values: ['unknown', 'Severe dysplasia', 'Normal or basal cell hyperplasia or metaplasia', 'Mild dysplasia', 'Carcinoma in Situ', 'Moderate dysplasia', '']

Label: AdjacentBiospecimenIDs
Description: List of HTAN Identifiers (separated by commas) of adjacent biospecimens cut from the same sample; for example HTA3_3000_3, HTA3_3000_4, ...

Label: TimepointLabel
Description: Label to identify the time point at which the clinical data or biospecimen was obtained (e.g. Baseline, End of Treatment, Overall survival, Final). NO PHI/PII INFORMATION IS ALLOWED.

Label: MethodofNucleicAcidIsolation
Description: Bulk RNA & DNA-seq specific: method used for nucleic acid isolation. E.g. Qiagen Allprep, Qiagen miRNAeasy. [Text - max length 100]

Label: PercentLymphocyteInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by lymphocytes in a solid tissue normal sample or specimen.

Label: HistologyAssessmentMedium
Description: The method of assessment used to characterize histology

Label: LysisBuffer
Description: scRNA-seq specific: Type of lysis buffer used

Label: HTANBiospecimenID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a biosample based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy_zzz)

Label: PercentNormalCells
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of normal cell content in a malignant tumor sample or specimen.

Label: SiteDataSource

Label: PercentNeutrophilInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by neutrophils in a tumor sample or specimen.

Label: FiducialMarker
Description: Imaging specific: fiducial markers for the alignment of images taken across multiple rounds of imaging.
Valid Values: ['Grid Slides - Hemocytometer', 'unknown', 'Not Reported', 'Nuclear Stain - DAPI', 'Other', 'Fluorescent Beads', 'Adhesive Markers', '']

Label: CollectionMedia
Description: Material Specimen is collected into post procedure

Label: HistologyAssessmentBy

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: PercentInflamInfiltration

Slide areas are named consecutively from top to bottom: A1, B1, C1, D1 for Visium slides with 6.5 mm Capture Area and A, B for CytAssist slides with 11 mm Capture Area. Both CytAssist slides with 6.5 mm Capture Area and Gateway Slides contain only two slide areas, A1 and D1.

Label: SlideID
Description: For Visium, it is the unique identifier printed on the label of each Visium slide. The serial number starts with V followed by a number which can range between one through five and ends with a dash and a three digit number, such as 123. For CosMx, this refers to the loaded Flow Cell ID. For Xenium, this ID indicates the slide orientation, as it matches the relative location of the ID on the physical Xenium slide.
